usage: olive_learn.py [-h] [-a ADAPT] [-c CHANNEL] [-C CLIENT_ID] [-d DOMAIN]
                      [-i INPUT] [-p PLUGIN] [-P PORT] [-s SERVER] [-S]
                      [-t TIMEOUT] [-T TRAIN] [-L THRESHOLD]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -a ADAPT, --adapt ADAPT
                        Adapt a plugin/domain, giving the new domain ADAPT
  -c CHANNEL, --channel CHANNEL
                        Learn from this channel of audio (defaults to 1).
  -C CLIENT_ID, --client-id CLIENT_ID
                        Experimental: the client_id to use
  -d DOMAIN, --domain DOMAIN
                        The domain to use
  -i INPUT, --input INPUT
                        Input data from INPUT.
  -p PLUGIN, --plugin PLUGIN
                        The plugin to use.
  -P PORT, --port PORT  The port to use.
  -s SERVER, --server SERVER
                        The machine the server is running on. Defaults to
                        localhost.
  -S, --serialized      Serialize audio file and send it to the server instead
                        of the decoded samples
  -t TIMEOUT, --timeout TIMEOUT
                        The timeout to use
  -T TRAIN, --train TRAIN
                        Train a plugin/domain, giving the new domain TRAIN
  -L THRESHOLD, --threshold THRESHOLD
                        Apply threshold THRESHOLD when scoring
